fields.description:
{html}<div><p>ResultSet should allow for retrieving the underlying data from
the DB if the author knows what type of data was stored. Get
methods for <code>int</code>, <code>float</code>,
<code>double</code>, <code>string</code> should be added and they
should accept a column index or a column name.</p>
<pre>
<code>
Add constants to Ti.Database
FIELD_TYPE_UNKNOWN = 0
FIELD_TYPE_STRING = 0;
FIELD_TYPE_INT = 1;
FIELD_TYPE_FLOAT = 2;
FIELD_TYPE_DOUBLE = 3;

Extend field, getField, fieldByName, and getFieldByName to take an optional second parameter which is one of the type constants above.

e.g. rs.field(1, Ti.Database.FIELD_TYPE_INT);
</code>
</pre>
<p>Drillbit tests and APIDoc must be added as well.</p></div>{html}
